Package: libgimp2.0
Architecture: any
Section: libs
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Replaces: libgimp1.3, gimp1.3-data, gimp-data (<< 2.0.0-6)
Conflicts: libgimp1.3, gimp1.3-data, gimp-data (<< 2.0.0-6)
Description: Libraries necessary to run the GIMP
 This package includes the developers' release of the libgimp and
 libgimpui libraries, necessary to run The GIMP.
 .
 It has been split off from the main gimp package in order to 
 facilitate easy development for packages that use libgimp and libgimpui,
 like SANE, the Scanner Access package for GIMP, as well as any other
 third-party plugins.

Package: gimp-helpbrowser
Architecture: any
Section: graphics
Conflicts: gimp (<< 2.0.2-6)
Replaces: gimp (<< 2.0.2-6)
Depends: gimp (= ${Source-Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: Built-in Help Browser plugin for The GIMP
 This package includes the browser for reading documentation for The GIMP,
 accessible from within the program.

Package: gimp-python
Architecture: any
Section: graphics
Conflicts: gimp (<< 2.0.2-6)
Replaces: gimp (<< 2.0.2-6)
Depends: python-gtk2 (>= 1.99.12), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${python:Depends}
Description: Python support and plugins for The GIMP, stable version 2.0
 This package includes the Python modules necessary to write Python-based
 plugins for The GIMP. It includes several plugins with various useful
 features.

Package: gimp-svg
Architecture: any
Section: graphics
Depends: gimp (= ${Source-Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: SVG plugin for The GIMP, stable version 2.0
 This package includes the plugin necessary for opening SVG (Scalable
 Vector Graphics) files in The GIMP.

Package: gimp
Architecture: any
Section: graphics
Depends: wget, gimp-data (= ${Source-Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}
Conflicts: gimp1.2 (<< 1.2.5-1), gimp1.3, gimp-nonfree, gimp-data (<< 2.0.2-4)
Replaces: gimp1.2 (<< 1.2.5-1), gimp1.3, gimp-nonfree, gimp-data (<< 2.0.2-4)
Provides: gimp2.0, gimp-nonfree
Recommends: gimp-svg
Suggests: gimp-help-en | gimp-help, gimp-python, libgimp-perl, gimp-data-extras, libasound2 (>= 1.0.0)
Description: The GNU Image Manipulation Program
 The GIMP lets you draw, paint, edit images, and much more! GIMP
 includes the functionality and plug-ins of other famous image
 editing and processing programs.
 .
 If you'd like to use a MIDI device as an input controller in GIMP,
 install libasound2 and read the how-to at /usr/share/doc/gimp/README.MIDI

Package: gimp-data
Architecture: all
Section: graphics
Conflicts: gimp1.2 (<< 1.2.5-1), gimp1.3-data, gimp (<< 2.0.2-4)
Replaces: gimp1.2 (<< 1.2.5-1), gimp1.3-data, gimp (<< 2.0.2-4)
Description: Data files for The GIMP
 This package contains architecture-independent supporting data files
 for use with The GIMP

Package: libgimp2.0-dev
Architecture: any
Section: libdevel
Depends: libgimp2.0 (= ${Source-Version}), libgtk2.0-dev (>= 2.4.4-1)
Conflicts: libgimp1.2-dev (<< 1.2.5-4), libgimp1.3-dev
Replaces: libgimp1.2-dev (<< 1.2.5-4), libgimp1.3-dev
Description: Headers and other files for compiling plugins for The GIMP
 This package contains the header files for the GNU Image Manipulation
 Program, along with the static versions of libgimp and libgimpui.
 It also includes the gimptool-2.0 utility.
 .
 Install this package if you wish to compile your own plugins,
 or if you wish to develop packages that use libgimp or libgimpui. 

Package: libgimp2.0-doc
Architecture: all
Section: doc
Depends: lynx | www-browser
Description: Documentation for the GIMP library, stable version 2.0
 This package contains the HTML documentation for the GIMP library in
 /usr/share/gtk-doc/html/ .

Package: gimp1.2
Architecture: all
Section: graphics
Depends: gimp (>= 1.2.5-1)
Description: Transitional dummy package for upgrading The GIMP
 The gimp1.2 package has been renamed to 'gimp'.  To make upgrades easy,
 this package simply depends on the proper version of 'gimp' to get the
 new packages automatically.
